itemDescription: Dawes, Elizabeth Anna Sophia (1864–1954), classical scholar and teacher

wikipedia_page.main: Elizabeth Anna Sophia Dawes (1864–1954) was a 19th-century British classical scholar and the first woman to receive a DLitt degree from the University of London.

response: * Elizabeth Dawes (1864-1954) – classical scholar and teacher, lived and taught in Weybridge from 1889 until her death
